# Actions Runner Controller (ARC) - Single ApplicationSet Implementation

## Key Facts:
- ✅ **Single ApplicationSet** - One deployment for both ARC components
- ✅ **Umbrella Chart approach** - One Helm chart with both controller and runner scale set
- ✅ **Easy to maintain** - Single configuration, single deployment
- ✅ **Logical grouping** - Interdependent components deployed together

## Repository Structure
```
├── infra/
│   └── templates/
│       └── arc.yaml                     # Single ArgoCD ApplicationSet (NEW)
├── arc/                                 # Umbrella Helm chart directory (NEW)
│   ├── Chart.yaml                       # References both official ARC charts
│   ├── values.yaml                      # Combined configuration
│   └── templates/
│       └── external-secret.yaml        # GitHub token secret
├── casissuer/                          # Existing example
├── cert-manager/                       # Existing example
└── cluster-config/                     # Existing
    └── **/config.json
```

## Files to Create

### 1. Single ApplicationSet

**File: `infra/templates/arc.yaml`**

```yaml
apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1
kind: ApplicationSet
metadata:
  name: arc
  namespace: argocd
spec:
  generators:
    - git:
        repoURL: {{ .Values.spec.source.repoURL }}
        revision: {{ .Values.spec.source.targetRevision }}
        files:
        - path: "cluster-config/**/config.json"
  template:
    metadata:
      name: '{{ "{{" }} cluster_id {{ "}}" }}-arc'
    spec:
      project: infra
      source: 
        repoURL: {{ .Values.spec.source.repoURL }}
        targetRevision: {{ .Values.spec.source.targetRevision }}
        path: arc
        helm:
          values: |
            project_id: '{{ "{{" }} project_id {{ "}}" }}'
            region: '{{ "{{" }} region {{ "}}" }}'
            cluster_id: '{{ "{{" }} cluster_id {{ "}}" }}'
            githubConfigUrl: "https://github.com/YOUR_ORG_OR_REPO"  # Update this
      destination:
        server: '{{ "{{" }} server {{ "}}" }}'
        namespace: arc-systems
      syncPolicy:
        automated:
          prune: true
          selfHeal: true
        syncOptions:
          - CreateNamespace=true
```

### 2. Umbrella Helm Chart

**File: `arc/Chart.yaml`**

```yaml
apiVersion: v2
name: arc
description: GitHub Actions Runner Controller - Complete Deployment
type: application
version: 0.1.0
appVersion: "0.12.1"
dependencies:
  - name: gha-runner-scale-set-controller
    version: "0.12.1"
    repository: "oci://ghcr.io/actions/actions-runner-controller-charts"
    condition: controller.enabled
  - name: gha-runner-scale-set
    version: "0.12.1"
    repository: "oci://ghcr.io/actions/actions-runner-controller-charts"
    condition: runnerSet.enabled
    alias: runners
```

**File: `arc/values.yaml`**

```yaml
# Global values - populated by ApplicationSet from config.json
project_id: ""
region: ""
cluster_id: ""
githubConfigUrl: ""

# Component toggles
controller:
  enabled: true
runnerSet:
  enabled: true

# External secret configuration
externalSecret:
  enabled: true
  secretName: "arc-github-token"
  secretStoreRef:
    name: "gcp-project-cluster-store"
    kind: "ClusterSecretStore"
  remoteRef:
    key: "arc-github-token"  # Update with your GCP Secret Manager path

# Controller configuration
gha-runner-scale-set-controller:
  replicaCount: 1
  
  image:
    repository: "ghcr.io/actions/gha-runner-scale-set-controller"
    tag: "0.12.1"
    pullPolicy: IfNotPresent
  
  # Enterprise-grade resource limits
  resources:
    limits:
      cpu: 1000m
      memory: 1Gi
    requests:
      cpu: 200m
      memory: 256Mi
  
  # Security hardening
  securityContext:
    runAsNonRoot: true
    runAsUser: 1000
    fsGroup: 1000
    seccompProfile:
      type: RuntimeDefault
  
  # High availability
  affinity:
    podAntiAffinity:
      preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
      - weight: 100
        podAffinityTerm:
          labelSelector:
            matchLabels:
              app.kubernetes.io/name: gha-runner-scale-set-controller
          topologyKey: kubernetes.io/hostname
  
  # Datadog labels for better observability
  podLabels:
    app.kubernetes.io/component: "arc-controller"
    datadog.service: "github-actions-controller"
    team: "devops"

# Runner Scale Set configuration
runners:
  # Use cluster-specific naming
  runnerScaleSetName: "enterprise-runners"
  
  # Reference external secret for GitHub token
  existingSecret: "arc-github-token"
  
  # Enterprise scaling configuration
  minRunners: 1              # Keep warm runners for faster job starts
  maxRunners: 50             # Scale for enterprise workloads
  
  # Runner pod template
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app.kubernetes.io/component: "arc-runner"
        datadog.service: "github-actions-runner"
        team: "devops"
    spec:
      # Security hardening
      securityContext:
        runAsNonRoot: true
        runAsUser: 1001
        fsGroup: 121
        seccompProfile:
          type: RuntimeDefault
      
      containers:
        - name: runner
          image: ghcr.io/actions/actions-runner:latest
          command: ["/home/runner/run.sh"]
          
          # Enterprise resource allocation
          resources:
            requests:
              cpu: "2"
              memory: "4Gi"
            limits:
              cpu: "4"
              memory: "8Gi"
          
          # Security context
          securityContext:
            runAsUser: 1001
            runAsGroup: 121
            allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
            readOnlyRootFilesystem: false
            capabilities:
              drop:
                - ALL
          
          # Environment variables
          env:
            - name: RUNNER_FEATURE_FLAG_EPHEMERAL
              value: "true"
            - name: RUNNER_GRACEFUL_STOP_TIMEOUT
              value: "300"
          
          # Volume mounts for performance
          volumeMounts:
            - name: work-volume
              mountPath: /home/runner/_work
            - name: tmp-volume
              mountPath: /tmp
      
      # Volumes
      volumes:
        - name: work-volume
          emptyDir:
            sizeLimit: "20Gi"
        - name: tmp-volume
          emptyDir:
            sizeLimit: "2Gi"
      
      # Node selection preferences
      affinity:
        nodeAffinity:
          preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
          - weight: 100
            preference:
              matchExpressions:
              - key: cloud.google.com/gke-nodepool
                operator: In
                values: ["default-pool"]
      
      # Graceful termination
      terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 300
      
      # Restart policy
      restartPolicy: Never
  
  # Listener configuration
  listenerTemplate:
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: listener
          securityContext:
            runAsUser: 1000
            runAsGroup: 1000
            allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
            readOnlyRootFilesystem: true
            capabilities:
              drop:
                - ALL
          
          # Resource allocation
          resources:
            requests:
              cpu: "100m"
              memory: "128Mi"
            limits:
              cpu: "500m"
              memory: "256Mi"
          
          # Temporary volume for read-only filesystem
          volumeMounts:
            - name: tmp-volume
              mountPath: /tmp
      
      volumes:
        - name: tmp-volume
          emptyDir:
            sizeLimit: "100Mi"
```

**File: `arc/templates/external-secret.yaml`**

```yaml
{{- if .Values.externalSecret.enabled }}
apiVersion: external-secrets.io/v1beta1
kind: ExternalSecret
metadata:
  name: {{ .Values.externalSecret.secretName }}
  namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}
spec:
  secretStoreRef:
    kind: {{ .Values.externalSecret.secretStoreRef.kind }}
    name: {{ .Values.externalSecret.secretStoreRef.name }}
  refreshInterval: 1h
  target:
    creationPolicy: Owner
    deletionPolicy: Retain
    name: {{ .Values.externalSecret.secretName }}
  data:
    - secretKey: github_token
      remoteRef:
        key: {{ .Values.externalSecret.remoteRef.key }}
{{- end }}
```

## Summary

This implementation creates:

1. **ONE ApplicationSet** (`infra/templates/arc.yaml`)
2. **ONE Helm chart directory** (`arc/`)  
3. **Umbrella chart** that deploys both ARC components together

No separate controller or runner ApplicationSets. Everything is unified into a single deployment.

